        "title": "refactor(whatsapp): introduce inbound message contexts",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR reorganizes WhatsApp `WebInboundMessage` so inbound callback data is grouped by what the data represents instead of being exposed as one large flat object.\n\nThe new shape separates inbound message facts into five explicit contexts:\n\n- `event`: message id, timestamp, and batching metadata\n- `payload`: message body, media, location, and structured payload context\n- `quote`: quoted/replied-to message context\n- `group`: group subject, participants, and mention metadata\n- `platform`: WhatsApp transport details and actions such as reply, media send, and typing\n\nDownstream WhatsApp auto-reply, monitor, identity, group gating, reaction, reply delivery, media, quote, and test-support code now reads these facts from the new contexts instead of the removed flat fields.\n\n## API Shape\n\nThis intentionally changes the `WebInboundMessage` callback shape. Code that receives a WhatsApp inbound message should read fields from the relevant context, for example `msg.payload.body`, `msg.event.id`, `msg.group?.mentions`, `msg.quote?.body`, and `msg.platform.reply(...)`.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/deliver-reply.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/ack-reaction.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/status-reaction.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply.web-auto-reply.last-route.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/web-auto-reply-utils.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/process-message.audio-preflight.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/group-gating.audio-preflight.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/group-gating.allowlist-warn.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/on-message.audio-preflight.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/monitor-inbox.behavior.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/inbound.media.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply.web-auto-reply.compresses-common-formats-jpeg-cap.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/inbound-dispatch.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/web-auto-reply-monitor.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/process-message.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply.web-auto-reply.connection-and-logging.e2e.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply.broadcast-groups.combined.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/inbound-context.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/inbound/access-control.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check origin/main..HEAD`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n\n## Review Note\n\nThe final auto-review finding was the expected public callback shape change: older code that reads flat fields such as `msg.body` or calls `msg.reply(...)` must move to the new contexts. I am treating that as intentional for this refactor rather than adding deprecated flat aliases back into the type.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: WhatsApp inbound callback messages now expose event, payload, quote, group, and platform contexts instead of one mixed flat object.\n\nReal environment tested: Local focused WhatsApp extension and e2e tests against latest `origin/main`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: The commands listed in Verification were run after the final rebase.\n\nEvidence after fix: Extension production typecheck passed, extension test typecheck passed, focused WhatsApp runtime tests passed across extension and e2e Vitest shards, and whitespace diff check passed.\n\nObserved result after fix: Inbound monitor and auto-reply tests consume the new nested message contexts for body, media, quote, group, event, platform reply, media send, and typing behavior.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live WhatsApp device/session behavior and broad Testbox/CI lanes.\n",
